</caption>
<paragraph id="3D7B160BDE61FF94D6E4FF00FC039F23" blockId="4.[166,1225,175,522]" pageId="4" pageNumber="207">
Diagnosis. Females of 
<taxonomicName id="FAC46D88DE61FF94D439FF1FFD789EA0" authority="Marusik &amp; Omelko, 2017" authorityName="Marusik &amp; Omelko" authorityYear="2017" box="[518,658,175,201]" class="Arachnida" family="Tetragnathidae" genus="Nediphya" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="4" pageNumber="207" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lehtineni" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis id="0FB0CA19DE61FF94D439FF1FFD789EA0" box="[518,658,175,201]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="207">N. lehtineni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="14837762DE61FF94D4A3FF00FD379EA3" box="[668,733,175,202]" pageId="4" pageNumber="207" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
differ from those of 
<taxonomicName id="FAC46D88DE61FF94D5E0FF1FFBAC9EA0" authority="Marusik &amp; Omelko, 2017" authorityName="Marusik &amp; Omelko" authorityYear="2017" box="[991,1094,175,201]" class="Arachnida" family="Tetragnathidae" genus="Nediphya" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="4" pageNumber="207" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lyleae" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis id="0FB0CA19DE61FF94D5E0FF1FFBAC9EA0" box="[991,1094,175,201]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="207">N. lyleae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="14837762DE61FF94D26EFF00FB789EA3" box="[1105,1170,175,202]" pageId="4" pageNumber="207" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
and 
<taxonomicName id="FAC46D88DE61FF94D699FF7FFEF99E80" authority="Marusik &amp; Omelko, 2017" authorityName="Marusik &amp; Omelko" authorityYear="2017" box="[166,275,207,233]" class="Arachnida" family="Tetragnathidae" genus="Nediphya" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="4" pageNumber="207" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hippai" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis id="0FB0CA19DE61FF94D699FF7FFEF99E80" box="[166,275,207,233]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="207">N. hippai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="14837762DE61FF94D726FF60FEBD9E83" box="[281,343,207,234]" pageId="4" pageNumber="207" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
by having lateral dark bands on the carapace 
<emphasis id="0FB0CA19DE61FF94D550FF7FFC6C9E80" box="[879,902,208,233]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="207">vs</emphasis>
. sublateral in the other two species. 
<taxonomicName id="FAC46D88DE61FF94D739FF40FE039F60" authority="Marusik &amp; Omelko, 2017" authorityName="Marusik &amp; Omelko" authorityYear="2017" box="[262,489,239,265]" class="Arachnida" family="Tetragnathidae" genus="Nediphya" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="4" pageNumber="207" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lehtineni" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis id="0FB0CA19DE61FF94D739FF40FE039F60" box="[262,489,239,265]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="207">Nediphya lehtineni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="14837762DE61FF94D7CFFF40FDC49F63" box="[496,558,239,266]" pageId="4" pageNumber="207" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
can be distinguished from 
<taxonomicName id="FAC46D88DE61FF94D551FF5FFC009F60" authority="Marusik &amp; Omelko, 2017" authorityName="Marusik &amp; Omelko" authorityYear="2017" box="[878,1002,239,265]" class="Arachnida" family="Tetragnathidae" genus="Nediphya" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="4" pageNumber="207" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="padillai" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis id="0FB0CA19DE61FF94D551FF5FFC009F60" box="[878,1002,239,265]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="207">N. padillai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="14837762DE61FF94D5CFFF40FBC49F63" box="[1008,1070,239,266]" pageId="4" pageNumber="207" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
(which has a similar carapace pattern) by the shape of the epigyne: the median plate in 
<taxonomicName id="FAC46D88DE61FF94D5C1FEBFFB6F9F40" authority="Marusik &amp; Omelko, 2017" authorityName="Marusik &amp; Omelko" authorityYear="2017" box="[1022,1157,271,297]" class="Arachnida" family="Tetragnathidae" genus="Nediphya" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="4" pageNumber="207" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lehtineni" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis id="0FB0CA19DE61FF94D5C1FEBFFB6F9F40" box="[1022,1157,271,297]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="207">N. lehtineni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="14837762DE61FF94D2B4FEA0FB229F43" box="[1163,1224,271,298]" pageId="4" pageNumber="207" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is almost as long as wide 
<emphasis id="0FB0CA19DE61FF94D7F4FE9FFE089F20" box="[459,482,304,329]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="207">vs</emphasis>
. 3 times wider than long in 
<taxonomicName id="FAC46D88DE61FF94D515FE9FFC4F9F20" authority="Marusik &amp; Omelko, 2017" authorityName="Marusik &amp; Omelko" authorityYear="2017" box="[810,933,303,329]" class="Arachnida" family="Tetragnathidae" genus="Nediphya" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="4" pageNumber="207" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="padillai" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis id="0FB0CA19DE61FF94D515FE9FFC4F9F20" box="[810,933,303,329]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="207">N. padillai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="14837762DE61FF94D593FE80FC039F23" box="[940,1001,303,330]" pageId="4" pageNumber="207" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="3D7B160BDE61FF94D6E4FEE0FCBA9C63" blockId="4.[166,1225,175,522]" pageId="4" pageNumber="207">
D e s c r i p t i o n. Male 
<typeStatus id="E27FA8A9DE61FF94D7DBFEE0FDA49F03" box="[484,590,335,362]" pageId="4" pageNumber="207">holotype</typeStatus>
. Total length 2.52, carapace 1.14 long, 0.95 wide. Carapace yellowish brown with wide dark brown lateral bands on thoracic part and thin light marginal stripe. Chelicerae yellow, with 3 prolateral and 3 retrolateral teeth. Sternum and maxillae yellow. Sternum subtriangular. Labium yellowish gray. Legs yellowish. Femora, tibiae, metatarsi grayish proximally. Abdomen with complicated pattern of spots and stripes dorsally and dark longitudinal stripes laterally.
</paragraph>
